        a(href=baseUrl + 'products-sub-pages/accessories-cables-pg3.html' type='button')
            |&nbsp 3
    br
    .row
        //-5
        .col.product-image
            img.product-photos(src='../src/photos/products-photos/taps.jpg' alt='Speed Selector Panel')
        .col.product-description
            h5 EVO/™ECM-TAPS (Speed Selector Panel)
            ul.product-subheading
                li
                    |Allows a service technician to field select the output of EC Motors.
                li
                    |Allows simple and economical selection of one of four pre-programmed flows.
                li
                    |The motor is programmed by the equipment manufacturer to provide the
                    | desired flow for each tap. The output is simply selected by moving the selector wire from one tap to another.
                li
                    |Boards may be ganged for more selections.
            a.btn.btn-secondary.products(href='https://drive.google.com/file/d/1KuFG-s4MW52t6LEnTnhU2rCpcdMQAs8g/view' target='_blank' type='button')
                |DATASHEET
    br
    .row
        //-6
        .col.product-image
            img.product-photos(src='../src/photos/products-photos/ECM-TAPx4-S0.JPG' alt='Four-Function Select Control Unit')
        .col.product-description
            h5 EVO™/ECM-TAPx4 (Four-Line, Four-Function Select Control Unit)
            p.product-subheading
                |The EVO/ECM-TAPx4 is a 4-line, diode multiplexed function select board that may be used 
                |to allow field selection of motor speed for up to four thermostat or automation controls lines.
            ul.product-subheading
                li
                    |Compatible with Regal Beloit's Genteq™ 2.3 and Eon™ motors.
                li
                    |Compatible with other devices that use diode multiplexing to select speed taps.
                li
                    |Features 4 tap lines selected by a thermostat or other 24Vac signal source.
                li
                    |For residential and commercial applications requiring field selection of motor output.
            a.btn.btn-secondary.products(href='https://drive.google.com/file/d/1L0ONULZ5_ycv5RcWe_m0mbajXPd1mCoA/view' target='_blank' type='button')
                |DATASHEET
    br
    .row
        //-7
        .col.product-image
            img.product-photos(src='../src/photos/products-photos/EVO_RSLW-S0.png' alt='Relay Switch')
        .col.product-description
            h5 EVO/™RLSW (Relay Switch)
            ul.product-subheading
                li
                    |Detects PWM or senses 0-10VDC signal thresholds to automatically switch equipment on/off in HVAC applications
                li
                    |Selectable switching voltage thresholds in 0-10V voltage sensitive relay mode
                li
                    |Built-in hysteresis to avoid contact chatter
            a.btn.btn-secondary.products(href='https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ydO92-_CkPxfNlO2GdedOhhOU0DLCq4A/view' target='_blank' type='button')
                |DATASHEET
    br
    .row
        //-8
        .col.product-image
            img.product-photos(src='../src/photos/products-photos/rly 4or.JPG' alt='4-Input OR Relay Control Unit')
        .col.product-description
            h5 EVO/™RLY-4OR (4-Input OR Relay Control Unit)
            ul.product-subheading
                li
                    |The EVO/RLY-4OR is a relay that is energized by applying 24Vac on any of four inputs.
                li
                    |The device is designed to allow thermostats and other 24Vac devices to energize an outside 
                    |air damper, valve, air cleaner, exhaust fan, ventilator, dehumidifier or other equipment 
                    |whenever the thermostat calls for any function.
                li
                    |With this device, energized inputs do not feed back into the de-energized circuits.
                li
                    |The EVO/RLY-4OR may also be used with automation controller outputs to provide a logic function or save automation outputs.
            a.btn.btn-secondary.products(href='https://drive.google.com/file/d/1sINTgxOEnARD6s5QPchOqvb_gDRHx5BH/view' target='_blank' type='button')
                |DATASHEET
    br
    .row
        //-9
        .col.product-image
            img.product-photos(src='../src/photos/products-photos/rnet.gif' alt='RNET Control Unit')
        .col.product-description
            h5 EVO/™RNet Control Unit
            p.product-subheading Allows a programmable HVAC or other PLC to monitor three contacts using a single analog input.
            ul.product-subheading
                li
                    |External or On-board Pull-up.
                li
                    |Small Footprint.
                li
                    |Header & Plug type Connectors.
            a.btn.btn-secondary.products(href='https://drive.google.com/file/d/1wVUN-lrqnpQkdYuOq1IpyYcjOjFuNbeI/view' target='_blank' type='button')
                |DATASHEET
